HEADWORD: Langue doc
<hw>Langue` d'oc"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., language
of <ets>oc</ets> yes.]</ety> <def>The dialect, closely akin to French,
formerly spoken south of the Loire (in which the word for
⟦ldquo⟧yes⟦rdquo⟧ was <tr>oc</tr>); Proven⟦cced⟧al.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

